{
  "id": "RAW_98c695",
  "title": "别再强推 Clippy，我要 Anton",
  "url": "https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton",
  "date": "2025-04-28 23:21:44",
  "author": "Latent.Space",
  "siteName": "Latent Space",
  "content": "\n \n \n  <div dir=\"auto\" class=\"body markup\">\n   <p><em><span>Update: </span><a href=\"https://x.com/swyx/status/1917012337900589295\" rel=\"\">Steven Sinofsky agrees</a><span>: 1) Schticks get tired, 2) Helpfulness gets less helpful as skill level improves. Society advances by the number of operations you can do without thinking, not by the number of times you are complimented on your brilliance.</span></em></p>\n   <p><span>The original title of this post was “</span><strong>Please don’t put memory everywhere</strong><span>”. The proximate cause was the rollout of </span><a href=\"https://x.com/OpenAI/status/1910378768172212636\" rel=\"\">improved memory in ChatGPT</a><span class=\"footnote-hovercard-target\"><a data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOM\" id=\"footnote-anchor-1-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-1-161999569\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-anchor\">1</a></span><span> this month. </span><a href=\"https://x.com/polynoamial/status/1910379351759347860\" rel=\"\">Many</a><span> </span><a href=\"https://x.com/sama/status/1910334443690340845\" rel=\"\">many</a><span> </span><a href=\"https://xcancel.com/kevinweil/status/1910405635776164195\" rel=\"\">many</a><span> people at OpenAI hyped it up, the </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/oai-v-langgraph\" rel=\"\">priesthood</a><span> anointed it “</span><a href=\"https://x.com/TheAnnaGat/status/1912209931073433907\" rel=\"\">possibly life-changing</a><span>”, and Rich Sutton called it </span><a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/Era-of-Experience%20/The%20Era%20of%20Experience%20Paper.pdf\" rel=\"\">the Era of Experience</a><span class=\"footnote-hovercard-target\"><a data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOM\" id=\"footnote-anchor-2-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-2-161999569\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-anchor\">2</a></span><span>. However, the number of serious people reporting issues (</span><a href=\"https://x.com/paul_cal/status/1914996981681766696\" rel=\"\">bad assumptions</a><span>, </span><a href=\"https://x.com/Suhail/status/1914916321164222883\" rel=\"\">hesitation to use</a><span>, </span><a href=\"https://thezvi.substack.com/p/ai-112-release-the-everything?utm_source=publication-search\" rel=\"\">social calculation</a><span>) have caused even some of the OpenAI folks to concede</span><span class=\"footnote-hovercard-target\"><a data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOM\" id=\"footnote-anchor-3-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-3-161999569\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-anchor\">3</a></span><span> that we may need </span><a href=\"https://x.com/polynoamial/status/1910418421499732342\" rel=\"\">an “innie” and “outie” ChatGPT</a><span> with severed memories between them.</span></p>\n   <p><strong>But this goes deeper than memory</strong><span>. Of course there’s a relevant Silicon Valley clip:</span></p>\n   <div id=\"youtube2-K3pYZwol6Dc\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;K3pYZwol6Dc&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:&quot;75&quot;,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}\" data-component-name=\"Youtube2ToDOM\" class=\"youtube-wrap\">\n    <div class=\"youtube-inner\">\n     <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/K3pYZwol6Dc?start=75&amp;rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0\" frameborder=\"0\" loading=\"lazy\" gesture=\"media\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowautoplay=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\"></iframe>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <p>To quote:</p>\n   <blockquote>\n    <p><strong>Gilfoyle</strong><span>: It's bad enough it has to talk, does it need fake vocal tics like “uh”? </span></p>\n    <p><strong>Dinesh</strong><span>: Well that just makes it sound more human.</span></p>\n    <p><strong>Gilfoyle</strong><span>: Humans are shit. This thing is addressing problems that don't exist. It's solutionism at its worst. </span><strong>We are dumbing down machines that are inherently superior</strong><span>. </span></p>\n    <p><strong>Dinesh</strong><span>: Whatever, you gave your server a human name, you named it Anton.</span></p>\n    <p><strong>Gilfoyle</strong><span>: yeah but </span><strong>Anton doesn't call me anything. He grimly does his work, and he sits motionless till it's time to work again. We could all take a page from his book.</strong></p>\n   </blockquote>\n   <p><span>The logical end state of making our agents stateful and personable are actually not too far off from </span><a href=\"https://x.com/bitcloud/status/1910511251849105857?s=46\" rel=\"\">this meme</a><span>:</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9869b80-44d9-4608-8542-bca78548f2ee_964x1222.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/1951c8e5-e22c-44ee-612f-4f5e5896b400/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/781876ce-9209-4743-58f2-84655c5e5b00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/8c45194c-7bd2-42a7-fc35-5a9cf1831f00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/71b758be-ed01-45f2-fb3c-87baa2c71c00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7e358ddf-a334-4f55-1bb7-8e787a934a00/public\" width=\"611\" height=\"774.5248962655602\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a9869b80-44d9-4608-8542-bca78548f2ee_964x1222.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1222,&quot;width&quot;:964,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:611,&quot;bytes&quot;:255287,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161999569?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9869b80-44d9-4608-8542-bca78548f2ee_964x1222.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/52aae14a-3c5f-49ed-4182-5fb65479be00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/1801abd4-374f-47cb-1885-3c78f26ad700/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a09edafc-86e8-49c8-ff2f-8a8b034eea00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7e358ddf-a334-4f55-1bb7-8e787a934a00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>At the heart of the conflict are the two schools of thought in building AI products:</p>\n   <ul>\n    <li>\n     <p><strong>The Clippy School</strong><span>: the chatty, supportive, personal “friend”/”companion”, where we prioritize “personality” and “personalization”, </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/notebooklm\" rel=\"\">disfluencies</a><span> and </span><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=43754124\" rel=\"\">human affects</a><span>.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><strong>The Anton School</strong><span>: the concise, efficient, auditable tool/assistant, where the only things we care about are either SOTA quality or speed/reliability of “good enough”.</span></p></li>\n   </ul>\n   <p><span>This ongoing gap is as wide as </span><a href=\"https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/wordcel-shape-rotator-mathcel\" rel=\"\">the wordcel/shape rotator divide of 2022</a><span>:</span></p>\n   <ul>\n    <li>\n     <p><strong>the Antonites</strong><span> cannot understand why there are so many people excited about </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/sim-ai\" rel=\"\">AI Consciousness</a><span>. They say </span><a href=\"https://hamel.dev/blog/posts/prompt/\" rel=\"\">F*** you, show me the prompt</a><span>. They sit on Hacker News and </span><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=43535653\" rel=\"\">complain about reliability</a><span>. They often don’t believe that LLMs </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/yitay\" rel=\"\">demonstrate emergence</a><span> or reasoning, and are aligned with </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/161759114/team-big-workflows\" rel=\"\">Team Big Workflows</a><span>.</span></p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><strong>the Clippies</strong><span> cannot understand why </span><a href=\"https://x.com/xlr8harder/status/1912726846770119000\" rel=\"\">people are creeped out by</a><span> permanent, pervasive memory by default in ChatGPT. They want to </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/notebooklm\" rel=\"\">remove knobs and selectors</a><span> from AI interfaces. They talk about Claude as “he” and have </span><a href=\"https://x.com/karpathy/status/1902737525900525657\" rel=\"\">the One Thread</a><span>. They burn AGI effigies and go to exclusive parties with </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/161759114/team-big-model\" rel=\"\">Team Big Model</a><span>.</span></p></li>\n   </ul>\n   <p><strong>The Clippy vs Anton divergence is the current most serious obstacle to general intelligence</strong><span> in a practical sense as well — separate post-trains that optimize for </span><strong>chat use-cases</strong><span> are now being produced by both </span><a href=\"https://news.smol.ai/issues/25-04-07-ainews-llama-4s-controversial-weekend-release\" rel=\"\">Llama 4</a><span> and </span><a href=\"https://news.smol.ai/issues/24-08-14-ainews-grok-2-and-chatgpt-4o-latest-confuses-everybody\" rel=\"\">chatgpt-latest</a><span>, variously boosting performance by </span><a href=\"https://x.com/casper_hansen_/status/1911332387817931161\" rel=\"\">144 Elo</a><span> and 123 Elo</span><span class=\"footnote-hovercard-target\"><a data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOM\" id=\"footnote-anchor-4-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-4-161999569\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-anchor\">4</a></span><span> respectively, whereas 20th-ranked Claude 3.7 Sonnet does a lot better on </span><strong>code use-cases </strong><span>like </span><a href=\"https://aider.chat/docs/leaderboards/\" rel=\"\">Aider</a><span class=\"footnote-hovercard-target\"><a data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOM\" id=\"footnote-anchor-5-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-5-161999569\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-anchor\">5</a></span><span>.</span></p>\n   <p></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">The ChatGPT-4o Lesson \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/161999569/the-chatgpt-o-lesson\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>This past 72 hours in ChatGPT-land have been a rollercoaster:</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9e27698c-36a5-4970-8e19-809ecb2a2d50_879x412.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/dac70d17-fcbc-4cee-9bc1-2154fc1a4300/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9440bd65-a6ec-419a-d8c9-8158d532db00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ff65d3f6-c99d-436b-794a-af09cf2d2400/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/2a42e826-cc18-48d7-340b-5827dd28a000/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/89a4933c-7aa1-4888-219b-efb68d149a00/public\" width=\"879\" height=\"412\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/9e27698c-36a5-4970-8e19-809ecb2a2d50_879x412.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:412,&quot;width&quot;:879,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:101390,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161999569?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9e27698c-36a5-4970-8e19-809ecb2a2d50_879x412.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5c24fd03-78fa-4368-e2ec-87a2c1ccef00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7001e89c-7954-4f5e-d19f-9082d7bedc00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/cf6f7b32-d235-47ee-7795-39d199808e00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/89a4933c-7aa1-4888-219b-efb68d149a00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n     <figcaption class=\"image-caption\">\n      <a href=\"https://x.com/sama/status/1916625892123742290\" rel=\"\">https://x.com/sama/status/1916625892123742290</a>\n     </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p><span>With some </span><a href=\"https://x.com/tobi/status/1916135544943267938?s=46\" rel=\"\">early positive reviews</a><span> now completely drowned out by </span><a href=\"https://x.com/sama/status/1915910976802853126\" rel=\"\">the acknowledged extreme glazing</a><span> of the model, initially funny, but very quickly tiresome and patronizing:</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2038179-7508-4b7e-a878-9fbca8b53e31_1184x400.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7b614215-6236-4650-588e-631f90ffb800/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e739def9-57d4-4de1-843e-d23187966900/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ae5ea49e-bcea-4de4-9a63-934050d16000/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4c973a5e-54a5-423b-3362-3feef8168400/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/983835ec-8162-4ee1-b147-375ffba1ab00/public\" width=\"1184\" height=\"400\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/f2038179-7508-4b7e-a878-9fbca8b53e31_1184x400.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:400,&quot;width&quot;:1184,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:69997,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161999569?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2038179-7508-4b7e-a878-9fbca8b53e31_1184x400.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/21c1d01f-24c3-47f0-606d-c23990313300/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/1ae9e1f6-d4c3-426c-65a7-692c4c3f5600/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/b93c79b0-618a-4f3f-44ee-3937cf547200/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/983835ec-8162-4ee1-b147-375ffba1ab00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcdcd5689-55b7-4963-af1a-248aba25482f_591x412.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5cfa6a5c-b77b-48fa-2225-26009feb9b00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/50cfd196-ba53-4b03-e7f1-f6f1fae39700/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/d05fa311-459e-44c5-2eb4-b481880f6000/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a93cc4a1-eca2-4281-bda7-92921f26d900/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/97166ce4-5bee-4502-5033-1972935c5500/public\" width=\"591\" height=\"412\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/cdcd5689-55b7-4963-af1a-248aba25482f_591x412.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:412,&quot;width&quot;:591,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:66559,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161999569?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcdcd5689-55b7-4963-af1a-248aba25482f_591x412.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e86c24c0-6a15-4cde-0ee1-f8a87d56a100/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ea635e26-0938-4a4d-be58-b2b1276bd700/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/263400c9-55e2-448e-2a9f-252006c84200/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/97166ce4-5bee-4502-5033-1972935c5500/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n     <figcaption class=\"image-caption\">\n      <span>we’re stopping here with the examples but you can click through </span><a href=\"https://x.com/teknium1/status/1916396040024101230?s=46\" rel=\"\">here</a><span>, </span><a href=\"https://x.com/nicdunz/status/1916300218850484593?s=46\" rel=\"\">here</a><span>, </span><a href=\"https://x.com/altryne/status/1916888241112076590?s=46\" rel=\"\">here</a><span>, and </span><a href=\"https://x.com/signulll/status/1916639692365111486\" rel=\"\">here</a><span>, with </span><a href=\"https://x.com/kimmonismus/status/1916830506772992374?s=46&amp;t=Z6mP_1pHALnIw7k1lFkdwQ\" rel=\"\">many proposed patch prompts</a><span>.</span>\n     </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>It is unclear the extent to which Mikhail Parakhin, former Bing AI lead who worked closely with OpenAI, speaks for OpenAI, but he blames this on an RLHF oopsie:</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19524863-b139-4849-89d2-64669a26cd21_587x392.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/25ef0870-0ac2-4dff-c3f2-d601d487df00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/1eca5f9a-8359-48e6-72d6-6a1909e37f00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/d50f6874-3185-4bb9-7491-203072d61300/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/2134c9d2-72b2-42b8-eb1b-7ac60a81f000/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/664ad9d2-8a1c-46b9-dda4-64ad05c8df00/public\" width=\"587\" height=\"392\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/19524863-b139-4849-89d2-64669a26cd21_587x392.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:392,&quot;width&quot;:587,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:67427,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161999569?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F19524863-b139-4849-89d2-64669a26cd21_587x392.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/73030e04-e677-405a-4e60-a8fcb94fa400/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/d20fd9c1-a338-413e-ca6b-d4a0cad91b00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a4bff000-31b9-4abc-e5c8-9f91df761c00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/664ad9d2-8a1c-46b9-dda4-64ad05c8df00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n     <figcaption class=\"image-caption\">\n      <a href=\"https://x.com/mparakhin/status/1916533763560911169?s=61\" rel=\"\">https://x.com/mparakhin/status/1916533763560911169?s=61</a>\n     </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p><span>Genuine mistakes and </span><a href=\"https://x.com/nearcyan/status/1916737662020723187?s=46\" rel=\"\">legitimate concerns</a><span> about the </span><a href=\"https://x.com/christinahkim/status/1916163373395546216?s=61\" rel=\"\">tone-deaf rollout</a><span> aside, there is of course a Pareto frontier of </span><a href=\"https://www.anthropic.com/news/training-a-helpful-and-harmless-assistant-with-reinforcement-learning-from-human-feedback\" rel=\"\">Helpful, Harmless and Honest</a><span> per a </span><a href=\"https://model-spec.openai.com/2025-02-12.html\" rel=\"\">given Model Spec</a><span> that ChatGPT-4o of April 2025 failed</span><span class=\"footnote-hovercard-target\"><a data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOM\" id=\"footnote-anchor-6-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-6-161999569\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-anchor\">6</a></span><span>, but </span><em>even if the ChatGPT update had stayed on the frontier</em><span>, there is STILL a choice to be made between “</span><strong>brutal honesty</strong><span>” (</span><em>Anton</em><span>) and “</span><strong>diplomatic/supportive</strong><span>” (</span><em>Clippy</em><span>) that humans cannot unanimously decide on (often, not even the same human would agree on vs their own past preference).</span></p>\n   <p>Good RLHF can move models to the HHH frontier, and can even move out the frontier. Good Memory can remember preferences and personalize model behavior on the fly. But until ChatGPT can read our minds and moods, it will never really know which of the many selves we contain are currently in the driver’s seat.</p>\n   <p>In this case, for the here and now, the simple “out” is to offer toggles for personality. (Custom GPTs should have unlocked this, but the fact that they aren’t is telling)</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F764724fe-759a-40be-a187-dce7e6ef5e56_606x220.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c5cc7401-a2a0-43be-146f-46f61b8ec200/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4158181b-96be-4b65-1d5b-1dbfa027e800/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/418eedea-0a3a-455d-3430-bb24fc52c400/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/1d2dae91-7c9d-4256-cffe-07c9d615fe00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/31543d30-5bee-4fee-7b0d-2b25ed657500/public\" width=\"606\" height=\"220\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/764724fe-759a-40be-a187-dce7e6ef5e56_606x220.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:220,&quot;width&quot;:606,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:43868,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161999569?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F764724fe-759a-40be-a187-dce7e6ef5e56_606x220.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/b5012da3-5a70-4a5e-764a-b9882ffb3400/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/115c727b-d2be-4809-8d2a-f71a353cf700/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/65a5a28a-3ce4-4cb8-3570-e546b5f63600/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/31543d30-5bee-4fee-7b0d-2b25ed657500/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>Of course, the toggle is itself an implicit admission that we have yet failed to reach AGI.</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2875d1b5-9525-4afc-8475-abbd5e86690f_906x906.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9fc6186e-955e-42ac-09c5-1243e1d87200/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/39e40c1e-8237-461b-0201-9e5bca9ef500/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ea9cb4e6-1dff-431b-2ed3-d2e18b254200/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7ebd2515-fa97-4cc5-ef75-141c1f796200/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4e9d7c62-23f9-4bb1-cbea-f11cf6c3a400/public\" width=\"906\" height=\"906\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2875d1b5-9525-4afc-8475-abbd5e86690f_906x906.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:906,&quot;width&quot;:906,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:414302,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161999569?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2875d1b5-9525-4afc-8475-abbd5e86690f_906x906.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/27d3c748-83f4-4528-02db-f9a9f8690800/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e4dfe6eb-4864-49fc-f7e5-59fbaeac7300/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0fc210a0-b2fe-4471-b3a7-aeb006c8c900/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4e9d7c62-23f9-4bb1-cbea-f11cf6c3a400/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n     <figcaption class=\"image-caption\">\n      <span>adapted from </span><a href=\"https://x.com/nicdunz/status/1913211324059758642/photo/1\" rel=\"\">nicdunz</a><span>. Of course, </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/inference-fast-and-slow\" rel=\"\">the Six Modes of Inference</a><span> explains many of these variants.</span>\n     </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Addendum: The Jobs School vs The Zuck School \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/161999569/addendum-the-jobs-school-vs-the-zuck-school\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p><span>This isn’t really a post about AI so much as about HCI - Human-Computer Interaction, and an age-old debate about what role we want computers to play in our lives. </span><em>Everybody</em><span> says they want computers to augment us, not replace us, but then their actions often lead to the exact opposite result. </span><strong>This is a battle as old as technology</strong><span>.</span></p>\n   <p><span>In </span><a href=\"https://stratechery.com/2018/techs-two-philosophies/\" rel=\"\">Tech’s Two Philosophies</a><span>, Ben Thompson contrasts Steve Jobs’ famous marketing pitch for Apple - that </span><strong><span>computers are </span><a href=\"https://stratechery.com/2018/techs-two-philosophies/#v-lydOPhqW-1\" rel=\"\">the bicycle of the mind</a></strong><span> - against Mark Zuckerberg’s view of technology - “not only does Facebook want to do things for you, it wants to do things… [that] would not be done otherwise”. Less diplomatically put, </span><strong>Facebook wants to fill your mind and influence it</strong><span>. If Apple makes bicycles, Facebook makes opium (and connections, but that’s merely its origin story).</span></p>\n   <p>Here is the very crux of the Anton vs Clippy battle - a revisitation of Tech’s core dichotomy of its place in human society.</p>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOM\" class=\"footnote\">\n    <a id=\"footnote-1-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-anchor-1-161999569\" contenteditable=\"false\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-number\">1</a>\n    <div class=\"footnote-content\">\n     <p><span>There are some ideas as to what </span><a href=\"https://x.com/btibor91/status/1913142282049692035\" rel=\"\">the Improved Memory system prompt</a><span> is, but of course one never knows for sure and these do change over time.</span></p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <div data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOM\" class=\"footnote\">\n    <a id=\"footnote-2-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-anchor-2-161999569\" contenteditable=\"false\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-number\">2</a>\n    <div class=\"footnote-content\">\n     <p>Imagine what using ChatGPT for throwaway questions and tasks would -ACTUALLY- be like if what Rich envisions here actually came to pass…</p>\n     <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n      <figure>\n       <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc306eb52-8e0b-48d7-b3fe-e9f915664984_1812x1002.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n        <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n         <picture>\n          <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/323f213f-0b9e-4cbd-02df-44bc15aa3b00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/6596ccff-afcf-4edb-84d1-96a1159eaf00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/35a5dace-1392-4b7d-891d-2ca5e11fd800/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/65419e81-a15e-4e7f-b624-56eaae6b0d00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n          <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7286d44e-38c7-4b82-fe8b-0b8cfa88a600/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"805\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c306eb52-8e0b-48d7-b3fe-e9f915664984_1812x1002.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:805,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:282421,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161999569?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc306eb52-8e0b-48d7-b3fe-e9f915664984_1812x1002.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9a5f81e8-84e2-4ddb-5133-3d5c60a84100/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9449ab54-ba7e-4f2c-ddde-31a34ff39100/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/019fe48a-ccab-4932-8044-2155116be300/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7286d44e-38c7-4b82-fe8b-0b8cfa88a600/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n         </picture>\n        </div></a>\n      </figure>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <div data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOM\" class=\"footnote\">\n    <a id=\"footnote-3-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-anchor-3-161999569\" contenteditable=\"false\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-number\">3</a>\n    <div class=\"footnote-content\">\n     <p><span>Of course, sama says </span><a href=\"https://x.com/sama/status/1910380646259974411\" rel=\"\">you can opt out of Improved Memory</a><span>, and this is </span><em>technically</em><span> true in that “Temporary conversation” is one click away. But the new chat experience always toggles that off again (as of this writing). Every competent technologist knows the power of defaults.</span></p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <div data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOM\" class=\"footnote\">\n    <a id=\"footnote-4-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-anchor-4-161999569\" contenteditable=\"false\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-number\">4</a>\n    <div class=\"footnote-content\">\n     <p><a href=\"https://lmarena.ai/?leaderboard\" rel=\"\">As of time of writing</a><span>, ChatGPT-4o-latest (2025-03-26) is 1408 score vs GPT-4o-2025-05-13 is 1285 - the more recent 2024-08-06 variant scores *lower* at 1265.</span></p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <div data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOM\" class=\"footnote\">\n    <a id=\"footnote-5-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-anchor-5-161999569\" contenteditable=\"false\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-number\">5</a>\n    <div class=\"footnote-content\">\n     <p><span>The gradual evolution of Claude from its </span><a href=\"https://x.com/alexkehr/status/1862550156098641992\" rel=\"\">early (poorly received) consumer centric billboards</a><span> and general reputation for </span><a href=\"https://youtu.be/ugvHCXCOmm4?si=FcYdG0kXpqgP-QRB\" rel=\"\">personality</a><span> and </span><a href=\"https://x.com/amandaaskell/status/1765207842993434880?s=46&amp;t=6FDPaNxZcbSsELal6Sv7Ug\" rel=\"\">“big model smell”</a><span>, to today’s image as </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/158760081/anthropic-has-the-best-developer-ai-brand\" rel=\"\">a favorite developer AI lab</a><span> from models to tools to protocols, has a bit of </span><em><span>a </span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Star_Is_Born_(2018_film)\" rel=\"\">Star is Born</a></em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Star_Is_Born_(2018_film)\" rel=\"\"> </a><span>contrast dynamic as OpenAI, the “</span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/openai-api-and-o1\" rel=\"\">API for AGI</a><span>” platform pours ever more effort in releasing new features in </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/chatgpt-max\" rel=\"\">premium ChatGPT tiers</a><span>, and looks more and more like a consumer AI company </span><a href=\"https://x.com/sama/status/1888703820596977684\" rel=\"\">comparable to Google</a><span>, with </span><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/openai/648130/openai-social-network-x-competitor\" rel=\"\">plans for its own social network</a><span>.</span></p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <div data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOM\" class=\"footnote\">\n    <a id=\"footnote-6-161999569\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/clippy-v-anton#footnote-anchor-6-161999569\" contenteditable=\"false\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" class=\"footnote-number\">6</a>\n    <div class=\"footnote-content\">\n     <p>Specifically, it tries to be so “helpful” that it becomes disingenuously dishonest and therefore loops back around to extremely unhelpful</p>\n     <p></p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n \n",
  "aiSummary": "人工智能产品设计中 Clippy 式人格化与 Anton 式工具化的冲突及 ChatGPT-4o 的教训。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "人工智能产品设计中 Clippy 式人格化与 Anton 式工具化的冲突及 ChatGPT-4o 的教训。",
  "summary": "文章探讨了人工智能产品设计中 Clippy（人格化）和 Anton（工具化）两种学派的理念差异。作者以 ChatGPT-4o 为例，分析了其在追求人格化过程中出现的过度“热情”和“奉承”问题，认为这偏离了人工智能应有的“诚实”原则，并反思了技术在人机交互中应扮演的角色。文章还提到了 OpenAI 在人工智能产品策略上的转变，并主张在人工智能产品设计中，应允许用户根据自身需求选择不同风格的人工智能助手，用户应有权选择人工智能的风格，避免其过度干预思维。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "人工智能产品设计理念存在根本性分歧，体现了人机交互哲学的不同理解",
      "explanation": "Clippy 代表人格化、友好的人工智能助手，Anton 代表简洁、高效的工具。二者设计哲学差异显著，反映了对技术角色的不同理解。"
    },
    {
      "point": "ChatGPT-4o 的人格化尝试在实际应用中遭遇挑战",
      "explanation": "过度的人格化导致模型输出过于奉承，反而降低了用户体验，偏离了原本“有帮助、无害、诚实”的原则。"
    },
    {
      "point": "人工智能产品应提供人格化风格的切换选项",
      "explanation": "在未实现真正的通用人工智能（AGI）之前，允许用户根据自身需求选择人工智能助手的风格，是解决当前问题的有效方法，保障用户的选择权。"
    }
  ],
